      • SCALABILITY_MAXIMUM_TOKENS

        public static final String SCALABILITY_MAXIMUM_TOKENS
        A named preference that specifies the parser's token limit. Parsing will be aborted when a single translation unit has produced a maximum number of tokens. This is a heuristic that is used to detect translation units that are too complex to be handled the by the CDT parser.

        5.7
